President Trump has announced that he plans to appoint Joseph Otting, the current Comptroller of the Currency, as the Acting Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA). The current FHFA Director, Melvin Watt, has informed the White House that he will be leaving his position at the end of his term on January 6, 2019. Otting will assume the role of Acting Director until a permanent replacement is confirmed, while continuing to fulfill his responsibilities as Comptroller of the Currency.